ZH: 我不喜欢味道很重的烟。

EN: I don't like cigarettes that are too strong.

ZH: 他抽烟让我窒息。

EN: His smoking makes me suffocate.

ZH: 这烟看起来很难闻。

EN: This smoke looks very unpleasant.

ZH: 妈妈不让我碰烟。

EN: Mom doesn't allow me to touch cigarettes.

ZH: 他一天至少抽一包烟。

EN: He smokes at least a pack of cigarettes a day.

ZH: 烟的味道很刺鼻。

EN: The smell of smoke is very pungent.

ZH: 他烟瘾很大，几天不抽就难受。

EN: He is addicted to cigarettes and feels uncomfortable if he doesn't smoke for a few days.

ZH: 抽烟有害健康。

EN: Smoking is harmful to health.

ZH: 他的嘴边总是挂着烟。

EN: There is always a cigarette hanging on his lips.

ZH: 爷爷抽烟已经50年了。

EN: Grandpa has been smoking for 50 years.

ZH: 她身上总是散发着烟味。

EN: She always has the smell of smoke on her.

ZH: 他身上的衣服总是带着烟味。

EN: His clothes always smell of smoke.

ZH: 烟会让人容易上瘾。

EN: Smoking can be addictive.

ZH: 她把香烟点燃了。

EN: She lit the cigarette.

ZH: 烟雾弥漫整个房间。

EN: Smoke filled the entire room.

ZH: 他每天都会抽一两根烟能缓解压力。

EN: He smokes one or two cigarettes a day to relieve stress.

ZH: 烟会留下一股刺鼻的味道。

EN: Smoking leaves a pungent smell behind.

ZH: 她不离手的烟。

EN: She always has a cigarette in her hand.

ZH: 我受不了烟味。

EN: I can't stand the smell of smoke.
